## Steps

### step 1
id: read-encounter-header
instruction: On the encounter detail page, read the header: date of service (the page title), patient name, rendering provider, and payer shown as pill badges. Below is a status banner showing the current billing status and financial totals.
success_criteria: You understand who this encounter is for, which payer was billed, and the current status.
anchor: "encounter header"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Open an encounter from the Encounters list or patient record first.

### step 2
id: open-details-tab
instruction: Click the "Details" tab if not already active to see the claim information, payments, and any denials.
success_criteria: The Details tab is active. You can see sections for Claims, Payments, Issues (denials), and Coverage.
anchor: "Details"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The Details tab is one of three tabs at the top of the page.

### step 3
id: review-claim-lines
instruction: Click the claim card to expand it. Read the claim details: type (Professional/Institutional), total charge, diagnosis codes (ICD-10), and the line items table showing each CPT code with modifiers, units, billed charge, allowed amount, and paid amount.
success_criteria: You understand what was billed, the diagnoses documented, and payment breakdowns per line.
anchor: "Claims section"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The claim card is in the Claims section. Click it to expand and see line items.

### step 4
id: check-payments-and-denials
instruction: Read the Payments section to see remittances received. Check the Issues section (if visible) for any denials with CARC codes, amounts, and action buttons. Use the Activity tab to see the full timeline of what happened to this encounter.
success_criteria: You understand what was paid, what was denied, and the full billing history.
anchor: "Payments section"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Scroll down to see Payments and Issues sections. The Activity tab shows the full chronological timeline.

## Completion Message
you now have the full picture of this encounter — what was billed, what was paid, and any denials. use the action buttons on denials to manage them, or ask altair directly about anything you're unsure of.

